2012年9月12日，[[美國總統|美國總統]][[巴拉克·歐巴馬|巴拉克·歐巴馬]]在白宮發表聲明，譴責這種針對美國外交設施的「暴虐的攻擊行為」，{{注|1=原文："this outrageous attack"}}<ref name="White House">{{cite web |url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/12/remarks-president-deaths-us-embassy-staff-libya |title="Remarks by the President on the Death of U.S. Embassy Staff in Libya" |access-date=2016-01-31 |archive-date=2016-02-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201192152/http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/12/remarks-president-deaths-us-embassy-staff-libya |dead-url=yes }}.</ref>並表示「自建國以來，美國便維持尊重所有宗教的一貫理念。我們嚴正拒絕任何企圖詆毀他人宗教的行為。」{{注|1=原文："since our founding, the United States has been a nation that respects all faiths. We reject all efforts to denigrate the religious beliefs of others."}}<ref name="White House"/>接著，在提及「9/11攻擊事件」{{注|1=原文："the 9/11 attacks"}}、「在伊拉克及阿富汗的部隊做出了終極的犧牲」{{注|1=原文： "troops who made the ultimate sacrifice in Iraq and Afghanistan"}}，以及「而昨天晚上，我們從新聞報導上得知班加西攻擊一事」{{注|1=原文："then last night, we learned the news of this attack in Benghazi"}}等語後，<ref name="White House"/>歐巴馬總統強調「身為美國人，讓我們永遠不要忘記我們的自由之所以得以維持，是因為有人願意為之奮鬥、抵抗，在某些例子中，甚至願意為自由而獻身。」{{注|1=原文："As Americans, let us never, ever forget that our freedom is only sustained because there are people who are willing to fight for it, to stand up for it, and in some cases, lay down their lives for it."}}<ref name="White House"/>他繼續說道：「沒有任何恐怖攻擊能夠動搖這個偉大國家（指美國）的堅定信念，扭曲我們的人格，或是侵蝕我們所代表的價值。今天我們痛失了四位代表美國一切美好的同胞。我們將不會改變伸張正義的承諾。而且不要懷疑，正義將會得到伸張。」{{注|1=原文："No acts of terror will ever shake the resolve of this great nation, alter that character, or eclipse the light of the values that we stand for. Today we mourn four more Americans who represent the very best of the United States of America. We will not waver in our commitment to see that justice is done for this terrible act. And make no mistake, justice will be done"}}<ref name="White House"/>

攻擊事件過後，[[歐巴馬|歐巴馬]]總統指示加強全球所有外交設施的維安。<ref><cite class="citation web">[http://worldnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/09/12/13824089-us-ambassador-3-others-killed-in-attacks-on-libya-mission?lite "US won't rule out Islamist militant link to attack on US consulate in Libya"] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6BokfbuWk?url=http://worldnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/09/12/13824089-us-wont-rule-out-islamist-militant-link-to-attack-sends-forces-to-libya?lite |date=20121031052602 |dateformat=iso }}. </cite></ref>一支50人的{{Link-en|美國海軍陸戰隊保安團|Marine Corps Security Force Regiment}}派遣至利比亞以「支援維安工作。」<ref>[http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gcIr1Sc4OgaJdoyNtVSeGOGmgoeQ?docId=CNG.497e614aeca24eef8dd48ac8abcecab0.ea1 "US Marine anti-terrorism team heads to Libya: official"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gcIr1Sc4OgaJdoyNtVSeGOGmgoeQ?docId=CNG.497e614aeca24eef8dd48ac8abcecab0.ea1 |date=20130131000007 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.stripes.com/promotions/2.1066/marine-anti-terrorism-team-dispatched-to-libya-after-diplomats-killed-1.189072 "Marine anti-terrorism team dispatched to Libya after diplomats killed"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.stripes.com/promotions/2.1066/marine-anti-terrorism-team-dispatched-to-libya-after-diplomats-killed-1.189072 |date=20160213183139 }}. </cite></ref>[[聯邦調查局|聯邦調查局]]亦宣布會介入調查本案是否有預謀的可能性存在。<ref name="CBSNews"><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-202_162-57511645/u.s-launching-apparent-terrorist-hunt-in-libya/ "U.S. launching apparent terrorist hunt in Libya"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-202_162-57511645/u.s-launching-apparent-terrorist-hunt-in-libya/ |date=20120919201829 }}. </cite></ref>美國官員表示對利比亞的監視活動將會增加，其中包括以無人機的監視行為，以便「追蹤攻擊者。」<ref name="CBSNews"/>

國務卿[[希拉里·罗德姆·克林顿|希拉蕊]]亦於9月12日發表聲明，並將兇手形容為「持有重型火力的武裝份子」{{注|1=原文："heavily armed militants"}}，而且是「一支小型的野蠻團體－成員不是利比亞民眾或是政府。」{{注|1=原文："a small and savage group—not the people or government of Libya"}}<ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">Spetalnick, Matt; Hadeel Al Shalchi (September 12, 2012). </cite></ref>她亦重申「美國對宗教包容的承諾」{{注|1=原文："America's commitment to religious tolerance"}}，並說「部份民眾試圖為這起可憎的行為以及昨日於我國駐開羅的大使館前的遊行活動等事件尋求公道，以回應網路上煽動性的言論。」{{注|1=原文："Some have sought to justify this vicious behavior, along with the protest that took place at our Embassy in Cairo yesterday, as a response to inflammatory material posted on the Internet,"}}<ref>[http://www.state.gov/secretary/rm/2012/09/197654.htm Remarks on the Deaths of American Personnel in Benghazi, Libya] {{Wayback|url=http://www.state.gov/secretary/rm/2012/09/197654.htm |date=20161213165431 }}, Hillary Rodham Clinton, U.S. Department of State, September 12, 2012</ref>[[美國國務院|美國國務院]]於先前的要務報告中表明了以現有的預算增加大使館的維安人員數量將是一大挑戰。<ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">Solomon, John (September 12, 2012). </cite></ref>

9月12日，據報導[[美國海軍|美國海軍]]已派遣兩艘[[亞里·勃克級驅逐艦|亞里·勃克級驅逐艦]]（[[麦克福尔号驱逐舰|麥克福爾號]]及[[拉布恩号驱逐舰|拉布恩號]]）前往[[利比亞|利比亞]]。<ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://articles.cnn.com/2012-09-12/africa/world_africa_libya-us-ambassador-killed_1_benghazi-ali-suleiman-aujali-libyan-ambassador "U.S. vows to hunt down perpetrators of Benghazi attack"] {{Wayback|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2012-09-12/africa/world_africa_libya-us-ambassador-killed_1_benghazi-ali-suleiman-aujali-libyan-ambassador |date=20121004064734 }}. </cite></ref>兩艘驅逐艦上皆載有[[战斧式巡航导弹|戰斧式巡弋飛彈]]。[[美國|美國]]的[[無人航空載具|無人機]]也奉派至利比亞以尋找攻擊事件的主兇。<ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.cnn.com/2012/09/13/world/africa/libya-us-ambassador-killed/index.html?hpt=hp_t2 "U.S. struggles to determine whether Libya attack was planned"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/09/13/world/africa/libya-us-ambassador-killed/index.html?hpt=hp_t2 |date=20120913234449 }}. </cite></ref>

9月13日，[[歐巴馬|歐巴馬]]總統在[[科羅拉多州|科羅拉多州]][[戈尔登_(科罗拉多州)|戈爾登]]的一場演講中向四位「在利比亞外交駐所遇難的美國人」表達敬意，並表示「因為他們的犧牲，我們得以享受安全及自由的生活......我希望全世界的人們聽到這段話：致那些意圖傷害我們的人，沒有任何恐怖活動能逃過制裁。這些攻擊將無法暗淡我們驕傲地呈現在全世界面前的價值。」{{注|1=原文："We enjoy our security and our liberty because of the sacrifices they make ... I want people around the world to hear me: To all those who would do us harm, no act of terror will go unpunished. It will not dim the light of the values that we proudly present to the rest of the world."}}<ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/13/remarks-president-golden-co "Remarks by the President in Golden, CO"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/13/remarks-president-golden-co |date=20160112222701 }}. </cite></ref>

[[白宮新聞秘書|白宮新聞秘書]][[傑伊·卡尼|傑伊·卡尼]]在9月14日的白宮新聞簡報會上告訴記者「我們過去沒有、現在也沒有任何確切或堅實的證據證明這起事件（指攻擊事件）與影片（指《[[穆斯林的无知|穆斯林的無知]]》）無關。」{{注|1=原文："we don't have and did not have concrete evidence to suggest that this [the Benghazi attack] was not in reaction to the film."}}<ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/14/press-briefing-press-secretary-jay-carney-9142012 "Press Briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney, 9/14/2012"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/14/press-briefing-press-secretary-jay-carney-9142012 |date=20160220213943 }}. </cite></ref>他繼續說道：「沒有任何情資能夠協助我們避免這起事件發生。這是－我的意思是，我想[[國家情報總監|國家情報總監]]的發言人對報告錯誤一事講得非常詳細。那份報告認為我們在攻擊發生前便已接獲領事館可能會遭受攻擊的情報......我們手邊沒有任何資訊表明這起攻擊事件是有預謀的。我們在這個區域所見到的不穩定情緒主要是對這部影片的反應，而大多數的穆斯林都認為影片冒犯到他們了。雖然這種暴力行為應該要譴責，兇手也還沒落網，但就我們所知，它與911週年或是美國的政策都沒有關係。」{{注|1=原文："There was no intelligence that in any way could have been acted on to prevent these attacks. It is—I mean, I think the DNI spokesman was very declarative about this that the report is false. The report suggested that there was intelligence that was available prior to this that led us to believe that this facility would be attacked, and that is false ... We have no information to suggest that it was a preplanned attack. The unrest we've seen around the region has been in reaction to a video that Muslims, many Muslims find offensive. And while the violence is reprehensible and unjustified, it is not a reaction to the 9/11 anniversary that we know of, or to U.S. policy."}}

9月14日，4位遇難美國人的遺體運回[[美國|美國]]。[[歐巴馬|歐巴馬]]總統及國務卿[[希拉里·罗德姆·克林顿|希拉蕊]]皆出席了遺體轉移儀式。在她的致詞中，[[希拉里·罗德姆·克林顿|希拉蕊]]提到：「一位年輕的女性，她的臉已遮住，眼神中充滿了憂傷，奮力舉起一塊手寫的字板，上頭寫著：暴徒和殺人犯不能代表班加西或伊斯蘭。曾與克里斯（指史蒂文斯大使）在耶路撒冷密切合作過的巴勒斯坦當局首腦，寄了一封信給我，表達對他（史蒂文斯大使）的活力與正直感到懷念，而且對－我引述他的話－這個醜陋的暴行感到遺憾。」{{注|1=原文："One young woman, her head covered and her eyes haunted with sadness, held up a handwritten sign that said 'Thugs and killers don't represent Benghazi nor Islam.' The President of the Palestinian Authority, who worked closely with Chris when he served in Jerusalem, sent me a letter remembering his energy and integrity, and deploring—and I quote—'an act of ugly terror.'"}}<ref>[http://www.state.gov/secretary/rm/2012/09/197780.htm Remarks at the Transfer of Remains Ceremony to Honor Those Lost in Attacks in Benghazi, Libya] {{Wayback|url=http://www.state.gov/secretary/rm/2012/09/197780.htm |date=20170106121949 }}, Hillary Rodham Clinton, September 14, 2012</ref>她繼續說道：「我們看到了針對我國在班加西駐所的強力攻擊奪走了許多勇敢之人的生命。」{{注|1=原文："We've seen the heavy assault on our post in Benghazi that took the lives of those brave men."}}

9月16日，美國駐聯合國大使[[苏珊·赖斯|蘇珊·賴思]]出席美國五大週日脫口秀以評論攻擊事件。在出席之前，她收到中情局所提供的備忘錄，以協助她整理「談話要點」。中情局的備忘錄是這麼說的：<ref name="nyt22"><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">Schmitt, Eric (October 21, 2012). </cite></ref> {{quote|目前可用的資訊表明在班加西地區的示威活動是受到{{Link-ar|美國駐埃及大使館|سفارة الولايات المتحدة في مصر}}的遊行活動所自發影響，並且最終演變成一場針對班加西美國領事館以及附屬基地的直接突擊。有跡證顯示極端主義者介入了這場暴力示威活動。
這樣的評估可能會隨著更多資訊的蒐集與分析而有變數。調查仍然在進行，而美國政府也在與利比亞當局合作，以將應為美國公民的死負責的元兇緝捕歸案。{{注|1=原文：The currently available information suggests that the demonstrations in Benghazi were spontaneously inspired by the protests at the U.S. Embassy in Cairo and evolved into a direct assault against the U.S. diplomatic post in Benghazi and subsequently its annex. There are indications that extremists participated in the violent demonstrations.
This assessment may change as additional information is collected and analyzed and as currently available information continues to be evaluated. The investigation is ongoing, and the U.S. government is working with Libyan authorities to bring to justice those responsible for the deaths of U.S. citizens.}}<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/29/world/text-describing-an-attack.htmlText: The Benghazi Talking Points] ''[[纽约时报|The New York Times]]'' 28 November 2012</ref>
}}
利用這些談話要點為方針，賴斯談到：{{quote|根據至今我們所擁有的最佳資訊，截至目前為止我們的評估是班加西的攻擊是自發性的，而且受到幾個小時前開羅示威活動的影響，而當然，如你所知，在我國使館外的示威活動相當暴力－主要皆是因這部充滿仇恨的影片（穆斯林的無知）所激怒。但很快的，當自發性的示威活動也在我國駐班加西領事館外蔓延開來的時候，我們相信看起來極端主義份子及一般民眾都有牽涉其中--並使用，很不幸的，在後利比亞革命時代便唾手可得的重型武器。而情況也從原先的示威演變成更為暴力的活動。我們沒有--我們沒有能夠使我們相信這起事件是有預謀或是預先計畫的資訊。我想有極端主義份子涉入升溫的暴力行為中這件事是相當清楚的。不論他們是基地組織的分支、利比亞本土的極端主義者，抑或是基地組織本身，我想我們將會查清楚他們真正的身份。{{注|1=原文：Based on the best information we have to date, what our assessment is as of the present is in fact what began spontaneously in Benghazi as a reaction to what had transpired some hours earlier in Cairo where, of course, as you know, there was a violent protest outside of our embassy—sparked by this hateful video. But soon after that spontaneous protest began outside of our consulate in Benghazi, we believe that it looks like extremist elements, individuals, joined in that— in that effort with heavy weapons of the sort that are, unfortunately, readily now available in Libya post-revolution. And that it spun from there into something much, much more violent. We do not—we do not have information at present that leads us to conclude that this was premeditated or preplanned. I think it's clear that there were extremist elements that joined in and escalated the violence. Whether they were al Qaeda affiliates, whether they were Libyan-based extremists or al Qaeda itself I think is one of the things we'll have to determine.}}<ref name="Face the Nation"><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-3460_162-57513819/face-the-nation-transcripts-september-16-2012-libyan-pres-magariaf-amb-rice-and-sen-mccain/ ""Face the Nation" transcripts, September 16, 2012: Libyan Pres.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-3460_162-57513819/face-the-nation-transcripts-september-16-2012-libyan-pres-magariaf-amb-rice-and-sen-mccain/ |date=20120923014156 }}</cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2012/09/ambassador-susan-rice-libya-attack-not-premeditated/ "Ambassador Susan Rice: Libya Attack Not Premeditated"] {{Wayback|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2012/09/ambassador-susan-rice-libya-attack-not-premeditated/ |date=20120922065723 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/09/16/us-ambassador-rice-backs-administration-violence-sparked-by-anti-muslim-video/ "Ambassador Rice spends Sunday reinforcing White House position that Middle East violence was 'spontaneous'"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/09/16/us-ambassador-rice-backs-administration-violence-sparked-by-anti-muslim-video/ |date=20120922190726 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/1209/16/sotu.01.html "Transcripts, State of the Union with Candy Crowley, interview with Susan Rice"] {{Wayback|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/1209/16/sotu.01.html |date=20180122181723 }}. </cite></ref><ref name="Meet the Press"><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/49051097/ns/meet_the_press-transcripts/t/september-benjamin-netanyahu-susan-rice-keith-ellison-peter-king-bob-woodward-jeffrey-goldberg-andrea-mitchell/#.UF_LHI1lTng "September 16: Benjamin Netanyahu, Susan Rice, Keith Ellison, Peter King, Bob Woodward, Jeffrey Goldberg,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/49051097/ns/meet_the_press-transcripts/t/september-benjamin-netanyahu-susan-rice-keith-ellison-peter-king-bob-woodward-jeffrey-goldberg-andrea-mitchell/#.UF_LHI1lTng |date=20120920065903 }}. </cite></ref>}}在9月18日的白宮新聞簡報會上，[[白宮新聞秘書|白宮新聞秘書]][[傑伊·卡尼|傑伊·卡尼]]向記者解釋攻擊事件：「我說的是根據我們所擁有的資訊－我們最初的資訊，包括了所有資訊－我們無法找到能夠支持他人聲稱這起事件有預謀的指控；我們看到的是這部影片所點燃的怒火。這些是我們根據充足且堅實的證據所得出的結論。」{{注|1=原文："I'm saying that based on information that we—our initial information, and that includes all information—we saw no evidence to back up claims by others that this was a preplanned or premeditated attack; that we saw evidence that it was sparked by the reaction to this video. And that is what we know thus far based on the evidence, concrete evidence."}}<ref name="PSJC18SEP2012"><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/18/press-briefing-press-secretary-jay-carney-9182012 "Press Briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney, 9/18/2012"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/18/press-briefing-press-secretary-jay-carney-9182012 |date=20160313200403 }}. </cite></ref>

9月20日，[[白宮新聞秘書|白宮新聞秘書]][[傑伊·卡尼|傑伊·卡尼]]回答了關於公開聽證會中國家反恐中心主任{{link-en|馬修·奧爾森|Matthew G. Olsen)}}所提出「極端主義團體可能有涉入攻擊事件中」一事的提問。卡尼回應：「班加西事件，我想，是恐怖攻擊，這是不證自明的。我們的大使館受到暴力襲擊，結果是四位美國官員的死亡。所以，再說一次，這是不證自明的。」{{注|1=原文："It is, I think, self-evident that what happened in Benghazi was a terrorist attack. Our embassy was attacked violently, and the result was four deaths of American officials. So, again, that's self-evident."}}<ref>[http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/20/press-gaggle-press-secretary-jay-carney-en-route-miami-fl-9202012 Press Gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney en route Miami, FL, 9/20/2012] {{Wayback|url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2012/09/20/press-gaggle-press-secretary-jay-carney-en-route-miami-fl-9202012 |date=20160113021829 }}, White House, October 20, 2012</ref>同一天，在[[美國|美國]]國內一家[[西班牙語|西班牙語]]電視網<span>《Univision》</span>的節目上，[[歐巴馬|歐巴馬]]總統表示：「我們所知道的是，一場自然的示威活動因為一部糟糕的影片而升溫，而極端主義者藉此大做文章，以便趁機直接傷害美國的利益。」{{注|1=原文："What we do know is that the natural protests that arose because of the outrage over the video were used as an excuse by extremists to see if they can also directly harm U.S. interests."}}<ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/09/20/carney-elf-evident-benghazi-attack-was-terrorism/ "As Carney labels Libya strike terrorism, Obama continues to incorrectly cite anti-Islam film"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/09/20/carney-elf-evident-benghazi-attack-was-terrorism/ |date=20120921034427 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.mediaite.com/tv/obamas-responses-to-libya-questions-at-univision-forum-contradicted-by-reports-of-the-attack/ "Obama's Responses To Libya Questions At Univision Forum Contradicted By Reports Of The Attack"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mediaite.com/tv/obamas-responses-to-libya-questions-at-univision-forum-contradicted-by-reports-of-the-attack/ |date=20121025022442 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0912/81470.html "Obama pressed on failures at Univision forum"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0912/81470.html |date=20121010225653 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">Parsons, Christi (September 20, 2012). </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation news" contenteditable="false">[http://www.realclearpolitics.com/articles/2012/09/20/obamas_town_hall_meeting_on_univision_115533.html "Univision's Town Hall Meeting With President Obama"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.realclearpolitics.com/articles/2012/09/20/obamas_town_hall_meeting_on_univision_115533.html |date=20121004222951 }}. </cite></ref>

